Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.04,0:00:04.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even when encountering a huge wall, with friends it will soon become a large door.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.38,0:00:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today is a one hour special. A long awaited traveling play. A showdown at the Konpira theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.92,0:00:14.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seeing the one truth, while looking like a child, having the brains of an adult. His name is Detective Conan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.55,0:01:56.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, father. After we finally came to Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.92,0:01:55.80,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shikoku = Smallest of the four main islands of Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.80,0:01:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's better to eat rather than to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.55,0:02:01.93,Signs,,0,0,0,,"Sanuki" is the region name of Kagawa prefecture where udon noodles were first brought from China to Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.55,0:01:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sanuki Udon!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.85,0:02:05.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, okay... But before that, let me wet my lips a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.43,0:02:06.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,Udon = Thick wheat noodles, usually served in a hot broth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.60,0:02:09.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you do that, I won't be responsible if you fall asleep during the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.44,0:02:12.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. After we finally get to meet Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.78,0:02:15.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it already...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.53,0:02:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, the Kanemaruza theater where Tamandusuke and others are doing the play is really famous, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.86,0:02:20.62,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kanemaruza = The oldest kabuki theater still in use in Japan, was built at Konpira in the early 19th century.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.08,0:02:26.04,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kabuki = Japanese classical drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.08,0:02:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Every spring they perform the Konpira kabuki play...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.29,0:02:30.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and people around the nation come to see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.34,0:02:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, look, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.71,0:02:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're right. Amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.38,0:02:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to this!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.34,0:02:45.97,Title,,0,0,0,,The Phantom of the Theater
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.93,0:02:45.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.98,0:02:51.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is an udon restaurant?! It's just someone's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.65,0:02:53.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.90,0:02:59.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ohhh! Well, well! There seem to be snacks to go with the beer.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.32,0:03:01.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They are toppings for udon, father.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.99,0:03:03.49,Signs,,0,0,0,,Piping hot:\N{\b1}Hot{\b0} udon and {\b1}hot{\b0} fish soup\NHot and cold:\N{\b1}Hot{\b0} udon and {\b1}cold{\b0} fish soup\NCold and hot:\N{\b1}Cold{\b0} udon and {\b1}hot{\b0} fish soup\NLukewarm:
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.91,0:03:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:05.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, here they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.54,0:03:06.91,Signs,,0,0,0,,Tempura = Deep-fried fish and vegetables in a light batter.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.54,0:03:07.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tempura is over there, you may choose how much you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.29,0:03:14.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.17,0:03:19.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They just take your tongue with them! This is really the real taste.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:24.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This has really opened my eyes! It's come to this, so I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.97,0:03:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean that. That.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.18,0:03:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Sanuki Udon roaming eating contest?"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.27,0:03:32.81,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sanuki-Udon\Neating contest by trying the food at various restaurants
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.73,0:03:35.31,Signs,,0,0,0,,Start of the Temple road
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.73,0:03:37.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You two young ladies. Here, use these canes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.11,0:03:39.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Return them on your way down, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.36,0:03:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.11,0:03:42.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.03,0:03:46.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A cane? I'm not that old...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.33,0:03:54.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly, how many are there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.21,0:04:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see... To the Main Sanctuary there are 785 steps in total.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.09,0:04:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seven hundred...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.38,0:04:03.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And eighty-five.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.60,0:04:06.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.01,0:04:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should have used this from the beginning. Since there is something this useful!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.77,0:04:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Where is father?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.06,0:04:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.06,0:04:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.65,0:04:19.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As expected, local sake is on a different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.65,0:04:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.61,0:04:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What about the shrine visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.95,0:04:26.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Pray for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:32.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, Kanemaruza is right over there. I'll wait here. Obachan, one more!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.46,0:04:35.21,Signs,,0,0,0,,Obachan = Cuter version of obasan (an endearing term for an unrelated older woman)
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.04,0:04:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened to tasting udon at different restaurants?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.22,0:04:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm finally here. Carrying me only half-way is unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.98,0:04:55.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're slow, Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.94,0:04:58.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could've stayed down and rest with my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute! Don't compare me with him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.03,0:05:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Konpira{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} is a Sea's Guardian Deity, right-?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.74,0:05:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true. The people who work at sea receive courteous blessings; this says...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.62,0:05:13.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost time. Shall we go to the Kanemaruza?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.29,0:05:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting for this! I wonder if Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} is doing good?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.54,0:05:19.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.92,0:05:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. That's the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.76,0:05:25.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they like "love-love" yet, those two?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.97,0:05:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Target or not... Ah, Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.26,0:05:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.30,0:05:32.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haha... Every single person...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.56,0:05:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Welcome, all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.11,0:05:42.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You had a long way to walk. We can't thank you enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.57,0:05:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is hopeless.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.11,0:05:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:48.36,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kataoka Renge (17)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.86,0:05:48.36,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Itou Tamanosuke (17)\NChairman
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just look at them, all love-love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.45,0:05:50.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.12,0:05:52.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.99,0:05:53.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.29,0:05:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.91,0:05:58.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Itou Megumi (7)\NChild actor and Tamanosuke's little sister
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.50,0:05:58.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are no little kids today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.92,0:06:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you mean them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.63,0:06:02.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They had some things to do, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.75,0:06:04.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's good. Megumi is so happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.21,0:06:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.30,0:06:09.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This, this... Isn't the kid with glasses popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.93,0:06:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.14,0:06:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.60,0:06:18.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The entry way is low, so be careful with your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.06,0:06:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this about a low entrance...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.73,0:06:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.07,0:06:25.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you alright?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.11,0:06:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.53,0:06:33.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are still in the middle of preparations and a bit busy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Woah, how wonderful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.71,0:06:41.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, right now, at the stage, they are checking if the Seri is working.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.21,0:06:44.50,Signs,,0,0,0,,Seri
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.04,0:06:42.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seri?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.29,0:06:46.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Several people push it up from the basement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.51,0:06:49.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The actor comes out from there and takes a pose.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.55,0:06:56.39,Signs,,0,0,0,,Rotating Stage
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.55,0:06:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stage is moving!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.34,0:06:56.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a Rotating-Stage. Again, there are many people in the basement rotating it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.64,0:06:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the same method as in the olden days.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.43,0:07:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the basement, it's called "Naraku".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:06.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,Naraku = Theater basement, also means Hell
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:06.28,Signs,,0,0,0,,Naraku
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.31,0:07:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the olden days the drainage was bad, so the people in the basement had a hard time, hence that name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.11,0:07:09.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This road is called Hanamichi, the audience to stage passage!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.11,0:07:14.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hanamichi
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:13.66,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hanamichi = The passage through audience to stage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.28,0:07:13.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After a signal, the actor-goes through the audience to the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.58,0:07:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way, there is "Suppon". Just like Seri, it's lifted from below.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.54,0:07:26.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, right above the Hanamichi, there is a crane like "Kakesuji".
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.21,0:07:26.05,Signs,,0,0,0,,Kakesuji
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.50,0:07:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once connected, the actor can fly all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.17,0:07:30.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:36.39,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sakura = Cherry blossom
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.05,0:07:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ceiling is patterned with bamboo and from up there they make Sakura snow storms, like they used to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.34,0:07:36.85,Signs,,0,0,0,,Grape rack
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.85,0:07:40.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uwaa! It's like a time trip to 100 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:41.73,Signs,,0,0,0,,Balcony seats
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.39,0:07:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.85,0:07:43.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Far from 100 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:49.32,Signs,,0,0,0,,The Edo (or Tokugawa), period ran from 1603 to 1867.\NThe Tenpou period was from around 1830 to 1843.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Firstly, this Kanemaruza was built as a Shogun forte and office at the end of the Edo era at the Tenpou period.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:53.41,Signs,,0,0,0,,Shogun = Supreme general of the samurai, equivalent to a "general": A high officer in an army.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.61,0:07:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Becoming a partial payment of a debt, it became the best Japanese theater there is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.24,0:07:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To be able to do a play here... It really makes me feel like an actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.08,0:08:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, you two are all love-love...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.25,0:08:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko! Ah, I heard that you are performing the Phantom of the Opera today, but in a different era.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.67,0:08:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. A showy play in stage, an ugly face poorly hidden, a mysterious phantom and a sweet songstress.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.18,0:08:21.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And their love story develops to love and hatred, a fearful play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.31,0:08:25.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead of Opera... The Phantom of the Konpira!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.04,0:08:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Beloved daughter, sing! For your loved one, me, the angel of song, sing! Sing, I say!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.17,0:08:54.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, noble angel! Shining angel! Carry my soul to the heavens!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.84,0:08:56.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot sing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.26,0:09:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Open your eyes! That is a devil! A revengeful ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.43,0:09:04.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fantastic...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.64,0:09:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey. Who is that person?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.69,0:09:10.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who is supporting the play this time, Rausu Tatsuhiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.65,0:09:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sponsor, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.23,0:09:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Rausu..."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.65,0:09:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From Rausu Companies, Kansai, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.99,0:09:17.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I read about it in a newspaper...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:22.04,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Rausu Tatsuhiko (27)\NSponsor
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.78,0:09:23.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His father passed away and the young son was just recently appointed as the successor, or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.17,0:09:30.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, way. Oh, no. Why so suddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.96,0:09:34.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pleased to meet you, I'm Suzuki Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.42,0:09:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do your best, Renge.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.55,0:09:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes! Renge!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.89,0:09:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because this Rausu Tatsuhiko is with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.14,0:09:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you. But I have a small role in this play, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.77,0:09:53.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... The heroine songstress is Renge. If we negotiate about a change...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.28,0:09:54.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:57.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's decided by the chairman, me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:09:59.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not you, the sponsor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.99,0:10:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention, I'm not the phantom either.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.41,0:10:03.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.83,0:10:04.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Phantom?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.00,0:10:06.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not because the request isn't firm enough, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.58,0:10:08.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously not!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.67,0:10:12.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I only wanted to see my child-hood friend's hour of triumph.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:22.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Request. A change of heroine. A child-hood friend and a phantom. This is almost like...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.76,0:10:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Phantom of the Opera. Opera-za no kaijin, there's no way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.31,0:10:34.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child-hood friend of Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, huh... But isn't this...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.98,0:10:37.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be better if you would be a little more honest, Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.86,0:10:38.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.03,0:10:42.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you confess your feelings to Renge? You like her, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.45,0:10:43.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.58,0:10:47.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you stay hesitating, I'll steal her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.13,0:10:52.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love triangle!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.46,0:10:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.50,0:10:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't really mind, chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.42,0:10:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Changing roles with Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.68,0:11:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying? Stop joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.64,0:11:07.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you understand why you are in this?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.47,0:11:13.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. And as a long time fan of Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... Just sharing the stage with you will make me happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.56,0:11:15.57,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Karube Romi (22)\NActress
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.90,0:11:15.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.03,0:11:19.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a beauty! I feel like I've seen her somewhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.24,0:11:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Karube Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. A famous young actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.24,0:11:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She gladly accepted the heroines' role...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.20,0:11:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...my-brother said. He was sure that she would refuse, but she quickly said okay. That surprised him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.46,0:11:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well. Excuse me for my rudeness... Please, do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.80,0:11:41.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, my. Seems that I'm hated.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.51,0:11:47.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oops. It's so dark in here, I can't see well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:50.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone! Collect the performance piece by the sponsor{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.23,0:11:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Performance piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.48,0:11:55.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A filthy tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:12:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's luminous tape. Look! It's put on there as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:02.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're an intelligent boy, aren't you? That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.86,0:12:07.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the theatrical blackout, it's put here so that the actors don't get their positions wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.67,0:12:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Neither of them seems to be within your reach, Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.00,0:12:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's totally fine. I found a different target.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.34,0:12:19.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A different target?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.96,0:12:25.14,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kawatake Otoya (25)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.92,0:12:27.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Finally some rehearsal, huh? It's a stage of friendship. Well, I have no interest except for my own play.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.85,0:12:29.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somehow he's so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.93,0:12:31.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move, move! You're in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.68,0:12:32.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! We're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.60,0:12:36.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who let these in? It's not time for guests yet!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.65,0:12:38.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get the creeps from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:39.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.19,0:12:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry, Nabe{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. I forgot to introduce them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:45.86,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Nabeshima Katsuo (40)\NChief of stage setting
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.36,0:12:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here is the detective Mouri Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, and...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.45,0:12:47.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.87,0:12:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri Kogoro?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.08,0:12:50.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That famous...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.37,0:12:55.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm that famous Mouri Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.42,0:12:57.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, the daughter, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.67,0:12:58.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.96,0:12:59.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.80,0:13:02.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My dear Edogawa Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.84,0:13:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.92,0:13:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.80,0:13:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Suzuki Sonoko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.72,0:13:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever you are, I don't want you to get in the way. The predecessor was stricter.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.27,0:13:18.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad is dad. I'm me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:23.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if I didn't have this job, I'd be neck deep in debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.90,0:13:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should be thankful as well, for the chairman. Ok! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.99,0:13:29.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't get in the way now!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.29,0:13:35.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's start.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.79,0:13:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, could you bring my mouth wash from the back?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.37,0:13:40.63,Signs,,0,0,0,,The requested mouth wash is to keep her throat clear, not to freshen up her breath.{????}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:40.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:42.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan and the rest, go to the seats.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.21,0:13:43.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeees!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.65,0:14:06.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Are you alright? Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.24,0:14:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.91,0:14:14.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.08,0:14:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone... an ambulance... Call an ambulance!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that, chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.17,0:14:22.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're exaggerating. It wasn't anything serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.25,0:14:31.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just a scratch. But this is quite close to the audience. It won't be good publicity if this gets out.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.05,0:14:33.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit. Messing with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.72,0:14:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who did this? Clear up and fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.93,0:14:41.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I don't fix this soon, it won't make it to the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.11,0:14:44.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's the worst. He's got to be the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.19,0:14:47.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But first, treatment...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.57,0:14:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to backstage first, Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.91,0:14:53.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That rope, it seems like it's been severed with a sharp object.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.16,0:14:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom's doings?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.12,0:15:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's rubbish.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.54,0:15:02.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was just someone's prank.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.54,0:15:03.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.80,0:15:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it had worked, we actually might've had to change the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.88,0:15:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That won't happen. Somehow I want to fight this now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.34,0:15:16.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantoms or something are trying to make us wet our pants? I won't take it. Right, chairman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.81,0:15:20.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me... You're in the middle of something, but... A phantom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:22.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the phantom of the Konpira theater!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.02,0:15:24.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I said, that's...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.48,0:15:26.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, it's the title of this play, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.32,0:15:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the Konpira.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.99,0:15:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes... That's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.82,0:15:33.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. It's the chandelier. Chandelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.53,0:15:34.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That would be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.28,0:15:36.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Chandelier?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.45,0:15:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the play that will come to this stage as well, the Phantom of the Opera...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.88,0:15:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A chandelier falls right on the first heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:55.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not all. It's very similar to your situation! The setup of the people in the Phantom of the Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.89,0:16:00.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, just now Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said that the phantom's request isn't enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.52,0:16:06.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's the same as well. In the Phantom of the Opera, the phantom requests the change of the heroine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.19,0:16:13.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What could this mean? It seems like everyone is hiding something big from us...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.24,0:16:16.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. What to expect from a famous detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.91,0:16:22.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. I think it would be better to discuss this matter with Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.71,0:16:30.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, we thought they were just pranks, by someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:43.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doing really nothing, only showing up to scare people, that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.31,0:16:47.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To deliver these letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.86,0:16:53.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm... They are all... very alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.99,0:16:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What exactly does this mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.41,0:17:02.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wide participation, I have interest! To be stabbed and die a glorious death! Sanuki Konpira's Phantom".
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.41,0:17:03.66,Signs,,0,0,0,,Sanuki = An area in northern Shikoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.87,0:17:06.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Wide participation, I have interest." It's obviously about the play, isn't it...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.08,0:17:10.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To say, "To be stabbed and die a glorious death" does sound very play like...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it a code? About the "Sanuki" word.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.51,0:17:15.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nicely figured out, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.80,0:17:16.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sanuki?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.26,0:17:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This was so easy, it on the contrary bothers me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.43,0:17:30.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sanuki... Ah! I see! Reading Sanuki without-SA.\NRemoving SA syllables and then read it, right? Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:35.57,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hiragana = One of the Japanese syllabaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.94,0:17:33.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Change them all temporarily in hiragana, and it's easy to figure out.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.57,0:17:37.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And... take out the SA syllables, right? Doing that...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.66,0:17:39.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.66,0:17:41.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Change the heroine! To Renge!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.74,0:17:45.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is... Clearly a threatening letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.08,0:17:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we would always listen to each one, we couldn't make a play!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.38,0:17:53.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. But, if we ignore it, what happened just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.51,0:17:56.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning, it wasn't a simple mistake, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.30,0:18:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, I don't think this is over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.56,0:18:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Chairman. I'm doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.10,0:18:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's okay with Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.56,0:18:09.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, you might just be a real actress.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.27,0:18:11.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.98,0:18:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it really okay, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.28,0:18:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering the situation and the threatening letter, it doesn't seem to be personal...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.99,0:18:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if the rope's cut, we don't know if it was really on purpose until we check into it more closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.91,0:18:29.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's right. At this stage, if the police would make a move...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.25,0:18:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding to the play, we have to leave the decision to the chairman, Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.17,0:18:39.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it's decided. We go with these roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.80,0:18:42.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Today's premiere... I feel the same way for tomorrow's show.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.26,0:18:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want you all to do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.36,0:19:02.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Earnestly, beloved daughter!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.83,0:19:11.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Believe in me and sing! Who believes in me, shall not die!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.50,0:19:13.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.71,0:19:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please wait! Are you a god? Or else... a devil?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.51,0:19:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is a devil. Here is your punishment! The dweller of the world without light... of the world of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.64,0:19:31.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You foolish and rude youngster. Being cursed, you shall be!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.27,0:19:38.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My love, my spirit, if you desire to bind them, you shall become revengeful to the world of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.86,0:19:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm so touched...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.28,0:19:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew it... It's because father drank so much again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.58,0:19:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a while now, what is that woman looking at?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.75,0:19:51.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.88,0:19:57.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.01,0:20:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.72,0:20:07.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is it, screwing around?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.39,0:20:11.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.44,0:20:14.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? That voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.23,0:20:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's almost like...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.61,0:20:18.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A frog?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.45,0:20:22.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.82,0:20:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This too is alike, with the Phantom of the Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.99,0:20:26.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.21,0:20:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit... Where did it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.71,0:20:43.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain. Close the curtain. Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, come back here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.68,0:20:50.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.02,0:21:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the only path, but... None of the guests seem to have seen a phantom going through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.61,0:21:04.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why, exactly...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.25,0:21:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, brat! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.21,0:21:18.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ehh, umm... It was so high, it seemed interesting...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.00,0:21:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't an amusement park! Only staff personal are allowed here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.84,0:21:23.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.22,0:21:26.72,Signs,,0,0,0,,Karube Romi
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.84,0:21:26.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone changed Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s mouth wash?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:35.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She thought it was the same wash, then the curtain opened, and she went to the stage like that. And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.81,0:21:37.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's mean. Who would do such a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.69,0:21:39.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You, you can't think...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.27,0:21:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That doesn't matter. Right now I have to think what to do with this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.65,0:21:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You rehearsed with Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.91,0:21:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lines, you should know them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.49,0:21:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You don't mean I...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.66,0:21:55.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no time to grumble about trivial things. The customers are waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.75,0:22:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The curtain is down. In fifteen minutes, I'm raising the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.72,0:22:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.35,0:22:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A phantom? Obviously just someone spiteful...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.93,0:22:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other customers seem to think so too.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.52,0:22:20.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.40,0:22:26.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A dead end, huh? This is almost like a maze.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.49,0:22:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anxious, loved daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.54,0:22:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is not too good... Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.67,0:22:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...if I can. Be Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s substitute actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.93,0:22:51.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.89,0:22:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am... in luck with the angel of song.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.65,0:23:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one is here. What was that...?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.86,0:23:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one is here. What was that...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.91,0:23:16.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To have met that person, my heart has been filled with joy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.87,0:23:21.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that person is a dweller of darkness. I wish to be taken by that darkness...!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.75,0:23:27.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop this talk about the world of darkness. I shall guide you to the world where there's light!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.47,0:23:30.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wherever, as your friend...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.22,0:23:32.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.22,0:23:36.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, swear. You will only love me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.47,0:23:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall swear. I will only love you!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.56,0:23:44.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You cannot go back anymore!\NYou shall die on this road!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.07,0:23:48.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Everything will end, everything will vanish in the darkness! Like this oath!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.99,0:23:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I shall not fear your true appearance. What I fear is that warped heart of yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.33,0:23:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Amazing, Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.83,0:23:59.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wouldn't think she was a substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.87,0:24:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huge success, Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.75,0:24:04.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That substitute's acting was magnificent, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.96,0:24:07.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to tomorrow's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.02,0:24:25.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This place gives me the creeps...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.96,0:24:48.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is...! What on earth...?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.38,0:24:52.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nabe{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.84,0:24:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't move! Don't move from there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.05,0:24:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No! You're wrong! It wasn't me! It wasn't me!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.27,0:25:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say? Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was apprehended by the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.90,0:25:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.65,0:25:15.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Save... Conan... My brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.82,0:25:16.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Megumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.24,0:25:18.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why on earth was he taken in for?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.08,0:25:22.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is... The stage setter, Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... They say he killed him!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.04,0:25:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} would do something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.30,0:25:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, they said that he was found unconscious next to Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, holding a knife.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.59,0:25:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean he had fainted?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.09,0:25:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he was also wearing the phantom's mask, which was covered in blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.47,0:25:45.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So they are saying that every phantom incident until now was the chairman's doing!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.73,0:25:48.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no... Father. Let's go to the police immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.61,0:25:49.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.11,0:25:57.11,Signs,,0,0,0,,Interrogation Room 1
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.11,0:25:57.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were asked to come with a letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.53,0:26:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Be gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.16,0:26:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I want to put flowers to the small dying village. Stone monument's morning, at the base I will wait. Rausu"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.75,0:26:12.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could this also be a part of the Sanuki code?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.84,0:26:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's alike with that threatening letter from that phantom of the Konpira theater.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.88,0:26:17.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.18,0:26:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you put it in normal hiragana...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.68,0:26:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I want to talk about Renge. I will wait near the stone monument,"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.90,0:26:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, when you went to the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.28,0:26:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.20,0:26:45.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why would someone do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.95,0:26:49.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because he's the phantom of the Konpira.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.83,0:26:56.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get the heroine changed, sending threatening letters, dropping the paper lanterns on Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.84,0:27:00.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and changing her mouth wash... That's the only thing you can think of!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.26,0:27:07.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is saying the exact same thing. That you called him there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.98,0:27:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no! I'm not saying that Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is the phantom! Just... that he did call me there.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.48,0:27:17.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this, night?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.86,0:27:27.33,Signs,,0,0,0,,Be gone! I want to put flowers to the small dying village\NPublic park's morning, at the base I will wait\NTamanosuke
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.86,0:27:21.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A same kind of letter with the exact same content was delivered to Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.07,0:27:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only difference is, is that the park was a stone monument. And the sender, was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.62,0:27:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.41,0:27:32.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I went, alright. But Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} didn't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.83,0:27:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Obviously. Because at that time he was at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.55,0:27:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, did you meet or see anyone at the park?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.72,0:27:43.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the ease...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.02,0:27:49.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.06,0:27:56.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, you didn't notice Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, but you were at the park, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.57,0:27:57.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.45,0:28:04.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.28,0:28:08.29,Signs,,0,0,0,,Criminal affairs section\NKonpira murder affair and searching investigations.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.70,0:28:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-This is an honor, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! To be able to investigate with you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.08,0:28:17.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have evidence to suspect Itou Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, because he was holding a knife in his hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.88,0:28:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was unconscious, wasn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.55,0:28:25.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's possible that someone else made him hold it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.10,0:28:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.06,0:28:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it, that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.35,0:28:30.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, regarding about that...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.52,0:28:32.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed there was a bump at the back of his head...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.31,0:28:39.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he could've also fought with the victim, slipped and hit his head to the different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.36,0:28:41.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Different level?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.40,0:28:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.03,0:28:52.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. Right behind the fallen victim was a big memorial stone. The pedestal was the different level.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.21,0:28:56.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the motive for the crime...?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.75,0:28:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's obviously money.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.42,0:29:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They were staff for the previous chairman, and he wanted the chairman pay off his loan...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.34,0:29:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and the victim was pushing it a bit too much. And then, finally...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.76,0:29:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.85,0:29:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a lie, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.93,0:29:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing. This is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.39,0:29:20.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Framing Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} as the phantom of the Konpira and thus getting Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s feelings toward himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.90,0:29:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly weird. Because, from the beginning, those two were...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.57,0:29:29.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All love-love. Even though it's mortifying. He has no need to do such a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.78,0:29:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I'm saying... Isn't that exactly the reason Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.91,0:29:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't tell from a woman and a man by just looking the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.42,0:29:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The manuscript is impossible now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.88,0:29:45.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chairman is a suspect...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.80,0:29:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's such a shame.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.88,0:29:49.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She .wasn't,half-bad, Kataoka Renge.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.60,0:29:56.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You believe in Tamanousuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.31,0:30:01.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The chairman believed in me too. That's why I was Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s substitute.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.02,0:30:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.24,0:30:08.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I was scared. I thought I definitely couldn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.41,0:30:13.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the angel of song... the phantom encouraged me!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.45,0:30:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.70,0:30:16.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It isn't you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.96,0:30:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you doubting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.79,0:30:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't know! What or who should I believe? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.67,0:30:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you are in this much anguish, you should just quit this play!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.80,0:30:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge. I want you to live with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.06,0:30:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.14,0:30:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I apologize. I am now only worried about chairman and only that...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.27,0:30:42.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that so? I understand. Then tell this to that chairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.65,0:30:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a sponsor, the damage, is too great. It's regrettable, but as it is, I have to withdraw my hands from this.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.70,0:30:49.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.03,0:30:53.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, you are another stony. I will definitely not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.25,0:31:01.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. We had no intention to eavesdrop, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.00,0:31:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, is it really true? That the phantom encouraged you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.21,0:31:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I can't be honestly happy. Because of the encouragement, I did well with the play.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.80,0:31:13.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not true. It's your true talent.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.31,0:31:21.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But changing the heroine to the new one, it's the same again, isn't it? With the Phantom of the Opera.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.40,0:31:23.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. I'm afraid of that too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.77,0:31:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who exactly is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.90,0:31:29.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's not Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r} Then of course, Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.36,0:31:33.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or rather a real phantom? A ghost? A monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.03,0:31:35.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No. That can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.46,0:31:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.26,0:31:49.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.22,0:31:51.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.26,0:31:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. A wireless one. Probably with this...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.22,0:32:01.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth, I heard the phantom as well that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.52,0:32:05.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means... In other words...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.94,0:32:09.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It means that the phantom of the Konpira is not a ghost or a monster.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.40,0:32:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask my father again.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.41,0:32:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll come too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.57,0:32:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to hurry too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.75,0:32:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are things that were bothering me from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.58,0:32:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The threatening Sanuki letters. Imitating the Phantom of the Opera to the phantom of the Konpira's behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.34,0:32:34.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it either wanted to be found or someone witnessing it, I can understand the reasoning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.72,0:32:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But a murder is going one step too far. Maybe there's a hint there...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.81,0:32:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A difference in level, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.94,0:32:51.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the ideal place for the criminal to hide...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.42,0:33:11.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Father! Can't you do something?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.51,0:33:16.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After coming all this way... At this rate, Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sama{\r}'s stage will be forever gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.01,0:33:18.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't have to worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.43,0:33:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just now I got a call from Oonishi officer. Itou Tamanosuke was released as innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.52,0:33:30.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In exchange, Rausu Tatsuhiko was apprehended with circumstantial evidence, it seems.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.90,0:33:32.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This time there is no mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.36,0:33:36.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the cane that is used to climb the stone steps to the crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.66,0:33:40.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...they found not only the victim's fingerprints, but Rausu Tatsuhiko's as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.41,0:33:47.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We think that they fought and his fingerprints got on the cane. Moreover, from his car...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.92,0:33:58.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't joke around! I don't know about any cane! And I don't remember putting those things in my car!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.14,0:34:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At yesterday's premiere a certain phantom made an appearance and caused a huge uproar.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.23,0:34:07.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most of the guests thought it was part of the play, though...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.69,0:34:10.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Projector! Didn't you use that at that time, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.78,0:34:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... It was done like that! D-Don't joke! I wouldn't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.20,0:34:28.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you use a remote control, even from your seat you can control the projector, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.04,0:34:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.08,0:34:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, a tape-recorder and a transmitter. By hiding these, you did the phantoms voice to Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.38,0:34:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To get her moved. We even found the speaker near the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.47,0:34:48.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was all to get her feelings to yourself! That's why you framed Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. That's the way it is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.44,0:34:49.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't joke!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.52,0:34:54.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Brother! Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.86,0:34:54.15,Signs,,0,0,0,,Onii{\rHonorifics - Signs}-chan{\r}! = Honorable big brother, with a cute suffix.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.94,0:34:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I made you worry. And the others?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.57,0:34:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.78,0:35:02.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go. In any case, we have to think what to do with the show.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.32,0:35:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.50,0:35:08.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is, after all, that pedestal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.54,0:35:12.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the criminal attacked Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from up there...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.30,0:35:22.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right! Alibi... I have an alibi!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.35,0:35:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Too bad, but that also...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.97,0:35:29.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The speak practice in that park was a lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.81,0:35:32.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had been scared of being dropped from the role.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.48,0:35:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If I would be an important witness for the sponsor, Rausu..." she thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.90,0:35:40.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what she's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.86,0:35:44.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Why would she do such a thing...?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.66,0:35:46.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.20,0:35:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me. Could I go to the restroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.92,0:35:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more thing. The projector that played the phantom.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.00,0:35:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Controlling it with a remote controller... That's possible from somewhere else too.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.01,0:36:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. Like above the stage!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.80,0:36:02.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, officer.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:02.51,0:36:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you are Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.14,0:36:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told me to ask you something...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.64,0:36:10.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.73,0:36:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fingerprints on the cane?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.06,0:36:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that. They were on the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.27,0:36:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right. A different colored and shining like daylight. Well, it was a mark after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.36,0:36:23.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From which store did it come?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.07,0:36:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About that... There hasn't been a store to claim it as theirs...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.08,0:36:32.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was performance tape, I thought we would find it immediately, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.67,0:36:34.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Performance tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.96,0:36:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see... I figured it out. I figured out the real culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.97,0:36:44.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rausu Tatsuhiko has escaped!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.64,0:36:49.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm deeply sorry. When I looked away for a little moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.39,0:36:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Call an alarm! Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.32,0:37:06.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You do not love me! Don't love me, don't love me!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.24,0:37:07.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.37,0:37:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you shall have a destiny with never leaving my side! Destiny of never leaving my side!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.55,0:37:32.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Leaving these on purpose is also the same. But why purposely tell their whereabouts...?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.48,0:37:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But there's nothing but to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.23,0:37:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}. You haven't seen Renge?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.52,0:37:39.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.69,0:37:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These are...! Don't tell me that Rausu...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.86,0:37:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were here! We looked for-you, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.45,0:37:47.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something the matter, you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.20,0:37:50.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.41,0:37:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.54,0:37:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.92,0:37:56.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.25,0:38:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rausu! Where is Renge? Wait, Rausu!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.09,0:38:08.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let us die together, loved daughter. Together fall to the world of darkness!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.68,0:38:10.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me go! Let me go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.35,0:38:12.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, phantom!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.06,0:38:17.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let her go!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.53,0:38:30.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.70,0:38:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop this immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.12,0:38:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sonoko...?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.12,0:38:42.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The phantom of the Konpira theatre... I know that you are not Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.42,0:38:47.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that from the start your intention wasn't a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:48.43,0:38:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right? Let's finish this already, Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.68,0:38:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.68,0:38:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.18,0:38:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right. From the beginning your behavior was strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.24,0:39:08.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was all your own charade!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.53,0:39:12.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was acting? Why would you...?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.62,0:39:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, to ensnare Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.25,0:39:26.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}... Why.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.42,0:39:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For revenge. To that man's father.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.38,0:39:32.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased Rausu Companies' predecessor, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.64,0:39:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of that predecessor my father's business was taken...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.68,0:39:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An illness that destroyed his body... Mother following him soon after...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.60,0:39:41.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.02,0:39:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being alone, the only thing I could do was to act!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.23,0:39:50.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First, I didn't think about a revenge... Then the offer for this play came.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.28,0:39:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even now... Even now! I feel like my parents are shouting from the other side!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.99,0:39:57.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then, my framing...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.41,0:40:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But at first, I had no intention to commit a murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.54,0:40:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least, I wanted to destroy this play...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.33,0:40:07.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...and drag the name of the sponsor, the Rausu Companies, to the mud. That would've sufficed!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.17,0:40:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then to put pressure on Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.47,0:40:16.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"This child can't do it. She will surely make a huge mistake at the stage", I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.56,0:40:22.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was a huge success. I had forgotten...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.15,0:40:29.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...that Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} is an actress. Like me, this child should have crumbled under the pressure...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.32,0:40:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On top of that, that man found me out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.54,0:40:43.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With this my loan is cleared, right? Your thoughts?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.63,0:40:48.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right... I couldn't forgive the wrongdoers about my mother and father.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.88,0:40:52.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I should kill this one and make him take the blame! That's what I decided to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.01,0:40:59.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you called Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to the trap, hiding yourself behind the memorial stone and waited.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.97,0:41:05.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the criminal would hit Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from that pedestal... A short person...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.23,0:41:14.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. For example, even a woman it would be possible to hit Nabeshima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} with a deadly blow to his neck.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.24,0:41:20.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That performance tape that was on the cane, is something Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} touched by coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.75,0:41:26.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You thought that the police would think...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.92,0:41:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...that Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was trying to steal Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} from Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} by framing him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.88,0:41:39.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, you showed yourself to Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.47,0:41:44.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By taking back your testimony later, you made the suspicion on Rausu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.06,0:41:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus, at the park while he was waiting for Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, you put the projector into his trunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.53,0:41:53.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...'But as expected, Rausu noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.74,0:42:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come out! I know the real culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.88,0:42:12.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's come to this, there is only one way for me, I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.88,0:42:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Escaping the police, Rausu and Renge{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} were forced to commit a double suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.84,0:42:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to have that little lady to see through it all...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.69,0:42:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't! Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.33,0:42:44.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You poor, misfortune man...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.13,0:42:57.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it! Tamanosuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.38,0:42:59.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.41,0:43:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Romi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. To take someone's life... Then even your own! Is that also because of your parents again?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.92,0:43:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever the circumstances, you've done something that a human should never do!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.63,0:43:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't just close your eyes on that. Dying is unforgivable!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.93,0:43:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And by leaving such an easy clue, the pamphlet of this place, didn't you want someone to stop you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.31,0:43:55.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To stop yourself from doing anything else...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.66,0:44:11.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a relief. All thanks to Sonoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.08,0:44:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I do it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.71,0:44:16.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were sleeping, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.67,0:44:22.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I will continue with acting. With the chairman, forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.55,0:44:23.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Renge...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.01,0:44:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.42,0:46:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.84,0:46:22.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This needs some serious kneading.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.63,0:46:24.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But somehow it feels good.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.30,0:46:30.47,Signs,,0,0,0,,Koshi = Hip; the body of a noodle (Wordplay)
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.30,0:46:31.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hip is more tired than this udon dough. At least give me some beer, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.68,0:46:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never changes.
